<h2>Skill Shop, Jukebox, and New Game+</h2>

Beyond the core platforming, Sonic Colors Demastered layers in <strong>progression systems</strong> that encourage replaying stages. The <strong>Skill Shop</strong> lets you spend collected rings and Red Rings to unlock new moves and customize Sonic's appearance — building your own moveset over time rather than having everything available from the start.

Earn an <strong>S-Rank</strong> on any stage and you unlock its track in the <strong>Jukebox mode</strong>, where you can listen to the game's fully original soundtrack. Every track was composed specifically for this fangame by Randomocity Remixes, KITSUN3POWR, Shoemonster, and David Johnson — no reused music from the official Sonic Colors.

Once you complete the demo's content, <strong>New Game+</strong> opens up: a fresh playthrough where all zones are unlocked from the start, every color power is available immediately, and the perfect homing attack comes pre-unlocked. It turns the entire game into an open playground for speedrunning and score chasing.

<h2>Sonic Colors Demastered FAQ</h2>

<div class="details-grid">
<details>
<summary>Is Sonic Colors Demastered free?</summary>
<p>Yes, completely free. The download includes both the game and its original soundtrack as a bonus ZIP file.</p>
</details>
<details>
<summary>How finished is the game?</summary>
<p>Version 0.5.4 represents roughly 65% of the planned content. The demo includes 25 levels across 5 zones, all 6 wisp powers, the Skill Shop, Jukebox mode, and New Game+. Development continues with more zones planned.</p>
</details>
<details>
<summary>Does it work with controllers?</summary>
<p>Yes. Full keyboard and controller support with complete button remapping available from the options menu.</p>
</details>
<details>
<summary>Why is the download 909 MB?</summary>
<p>The download includes both the game and a separate ZIP of the full original soundtrack. The combined file size exceeds typical fangame sizes but delivers a substantial amount of content.</p>
</details>
<details>
<summary>Is this related to Sonic Colors Ultimate?</summary>
<p>No. Sonic Colors Ultimate is Sega's official HD remaster of the Wii game. Demastered is an independent fan project that reimagines Colors as a 2D platformer with Rush-style mechanics and entirely original level design.</p>
</details>
<details>
<summary>Will my old saves work after updating?</summary>
<p>No. Updating to a new version resets save data. If you want to keep your progress, back up your save files before updating.</p>
</details>
</div>
